Let me explain that too. A 1600hp Heal over time has advantages and disadvantages over a direct heal. IMO Mage pets are very powerful and if you ever have to heal a pet during a 1 on 1 encounter with a mob then you are doing something wrong. Beastlords get heals because there pets need them. They do not tank nearly as well as mage pets. Mage pets have the advantage of tanking well while dishing out good damage. They do not have the option of chain casting so their pet dying is alot worse then a mage pet dying.  So a 2500hp heal will allow you to chain cast it with the 900hp heal making mobs like Yeldema and the like that much easier. <br>
<br>
If you play the mage correctly then do not fight something one on one that you and your pet can not take unless you intend to chain cast. I do not believe that VI should add heal spells in the game to allow the mage all types of play styles. A 2500hp heal will allow a mage to fight even harder mobs with only healing it. This could become a major problem when using the epic pet model.<br>
<br>
That aside the problem I have found is not healing during combat. If I am facing a mob one on one I never have to heal my epic pet. Over the course of 5 or 6 mobs his health drops low and it takes way to long for him to recover. A heal over time would help alot because we can heal the pet slowly during down time while having the advantage of medding during the time the pet is healing. If you are fighting something way to hard for you to tackle this heal will help but not overpower you during the encounter.<br>
<br>
2500hp heal I wouldn't turn down but it steps on BST toes and I don't want them stepping on ours so not going to step on theirs.  Those mages that do not have a epic have the option of summoning a new pet as oppose to healing them. I have to say that before i got my epic healing my fully armor pet was never a problem. I fought things that I could take down fast, easy and in bunchs. With epic healing is much more of a issue because it can not be chain cast. So giving us a 1600hp heal over time would help or they could just give us a quest that allowed us to convert Manifest Elements to a scroll. Then we could summon epic pet just like other pets and get the advantage of quick summoning and SCM3. I would take being able to chain cast epic over a 2500hp heal anyday =D.<br>
