<br>
My point in earlier posts was that since we can summon the elements, banish the elements, charm the elements, mez the elements, etc, I think we should be much better at healing the elements than we currently are. This is coming from a pure RP perspective. <br>
<br>
Raz, your points about balance are fair, but personally I'd like to see it come down to player preference rather than the math shown in your orginal post. If a player wants to RP a callous nuker who likes to send pets to their doom, go ahead, if a player wants to RP a pet cleric and keep the pet alive as long as possible, that should be an equal option, not a less efficient one.<br>
<br>
I did really like Jaytee's suggestion about a % based healing spell, I think this would be the most useful way to implement a healing spell for both combat and post combat. <br>
<br>
Casting CH on a pet after a fight would be useless, as it would put such a dent in your mana bar that you'd have to wait before fighting again. Using a 40% heal would give the pet a nice boost (epic or normal), then you can briefly med, and pet can briefly regen before the next fight.<br>
<br>
Ideally you should be able to heal your pet to about 60% without having to drop your mana bar below 60%.  (leaving rods out of this discussion for now). Pet regen rate should be about equivalent to a mage with KEI.<br>
<br>
Personally, I'd like to see both options implemented, perhaps the 40% heal at level 63, and the CH option at level 65.<br>
<br>
The 40% heal could be similar to the existing heal spells in both mana cost and cast time. (but can VI implement a % based heal other than CH?)<br>
<br>
The CH spell should take the same amount of time to cast as the level 60+ pets in PoP.<br>
<br>
One final suggestion would be to dramitically increase the drop rate on the current level 60 heal. Its really not an efficient spell, and not very deserving of its current low drop rate. The newer, more effective spells being debated here might warrant it however. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utezron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tezron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333333>(10/2/02 8:24:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> arg</span><hr size=1> ok here's the deal. <br>
