<br>
Some of you asking whats the difference between a complete heal that costs more mana than totally buffing pet?<br>
<br>
You know how much more powerful the pet is when fully buffed.  Whens the only time you need a big heal?  When it's taking big damage.   When is it taking big damage?  When its fighting big mobs.   If you don't have to chain cast pets that adds a bunch to the overall power you are pumping out.<br>
<br>
Say pets are 3 times as strong roughly when fully buffed.  If you have have to chain cast 7 pets the first one is very effective and the others are trash.  (Even if you somehow chain casted the epic, it would pop without it's damage shield.)<br>
<br>
Keeping one pet also means you don't get summoned, which again is huge for bigger mobs.<br>
<br>
And then of course theres a little problem of an AA we have becoming much more useless.  That would be pet mend.<br>
<br>
Even taking the star ruby idea, it means that if you wanted to you could solo much higher mobs easier.  It would suck for XP but the exercise would likely be for the mobs loot anyway.<br>
<br>
Am I against the idea of more pet healing / support over chain casting pets?  No way.  I hate the idea of chain casting pets.  Conceptually sounds more of a necro way to do things.  (Sending disposible minions by the dozens.)<br>
<br>
But I'm tired of people downplaying how powerful heals are in comparision to chain casts.  Simply put, it would make a huge difference in what we could do.  And yeah sure I want it too.  But those guys at Verant aren't dumb.  So don't argue it on the merit that is supposed to be &quot;exactly the same as summoning and buffing a new pet.&quot;  Its not. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucyricusbloodbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cyricus Bloodbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1071<br> <font color=#333333>(10/2/02 3:25:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://520013139003-001.bei.t-online.de/IWD_Human_Male_Wizard3.gif height=58 width=36></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: More pet heals..</span><hr size=1> I really like Wezloc´s idea <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><DIV style="position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=0000CC, strength=4)"><center><a style="font-family:Verdana; color:#FFFFFF; text-decoration: none; font-size:14pt" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3300>Sage Cyricus Bloodbane</a></center></div>
